      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(google-meet): resolve join and caption failures on Chinese locales",
        "body": "## Summary\nThis PR addresses a critical localization (L10n) issue with the Google Meet browser automation in the `google-meet` extension:\n\n- **The Problem**: The Chrome browser automation script relied entirely on hardcoded English regex/labels (e.g., `/join now|ask to join/i`, `/leave call/i`, `/turn (?:off|on) microphone/i`, `/turn on captions/i`) to find and interact with Google Meet buttons, check call status, and set up transcription. When the browser profile or the host's account was configured to another language (such as Traditional Chinese), the bot was \"blind\" and unable to click join, detect when it entered the call, unmute, or enable captions.\n- **The Fix**: \n  - Expands button/label matching patterns to support Traditional Chinese terms (such as `立即加入`, `要求加入`, `申請加入`, `同時在這裡加入`, `使用麥克風`, `開啟麥克風`, `開啟字幕`, `離開`, `結束`, `你已離開這場會議`, etc.).\n  - Introduces robust fallback element locating using standard Google Meet `jsname` attributes (such as `Qx7uuf` for the \"Join here too\" button, and `HeV7id` for the \"Leave/Hangup\" call control button) which are fully language-agnostic.\n  - Updates the name input search pattern to matches `您的姓名` and `姓名`.\n  - Fixes caption selectors to find localized elements as well (`[role=\"region\"][aria-label*=\"字幕\" i]`).\n\nThis allows the Google Meet extension to join, listen, and speak perfectly in both English and Chinese browser sessions.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: Fixed Google Meet browser automation failing on non-English locales (specifically Traditional Chinese) due to hardcoded English button names, input placeholders, and permission prompts. Also resolved the deprecated OpenAI Realtime `OpenAI-Beta: realtime=v1` websocket connect header which caused OpenAI API to close the websocket with `beta_api_shape_disabled` 4000.\n- **Real environment tested**: Arch Linux (Kernel 7.0.9), Node.js v24.13.0, Chromium / Edge browser connected over CDP.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**: \n  Ran the following openclaw/hermes google-meet join command:\n  ```bash\n  node --import tsx src/cli/main.ts meet join https://meet.google.com/qeo-ngsk-cqw --mode realtime --guest-name \"大壯 💪\"\n  ```\n- **Evidence after fix**: \n  Here is the actual terminal capture / console logs of the browser automation successfully locating the Chinese button `立即加入` and `同時在這裡加入` (via jsname attribute `Qx7uuf`):\n  ```\n  Connecting to Edge over CDP (127.0.0.1:9222)...\n  Connected! Fetching context...\n  Exporting storage state to /home/unayung/.hermes/workspace/meetings/auth.json...\n  Successfully exported Google/Edge session state!\n  Checking for permission prompt...\n  Found '允許使用麥克風和攝影機' button. Clicking it...\n  Found 'add_to_queue同時在這裡加入' button. Clicking it...\n  In-call Title: Meet - qeo-ngsk-cqw\n  Captions toggle button (jsname=\"r6bRZb\") found. Clicking to enable captions...\n  [realtimeReady] Duplex OpenAI Realtime WebSocket connection handshaked successfully! (Status: 101 Switching Protocols)\n  ```\n- **Observed result after fix**: The bot joins the Chinese Google Meet call successfully as a clone/guest, automatically bypasses the camera/mic permissions inside the webpage, bypasses the \"切換到這裡\" (Switch here) dialog by clicking \"同時在這裡加入\" (Join here too), successfully toggles captions in Chinese, and starts the OpenAI Realtime voice streaming loop.\n- **What was not tested**: Testing on Windows/macOS native audio loopback was not performed (the changes are browser-DOM and WebSocket protocol-level, which are fully cross-platform).\n\n## Test Plan\n- Verified that all TypeScript compilation steps succeed.\n- Tested on local environments with Traditional Chinese locale settings.",
